### Health check
GET http://127.0.0.1:8000/health

### Normal business query: employee lookup
POST http://127.0.0.1:8000/ask
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "question": "Fetch employee information for Priya Sharma"
}

### Knowledge base search
POST http://127.0.0.1:8000/ask
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "question": "What issue was addressed about checkout payments in the meeting?",
  "conversation_id": "demo-conversation"
}

### Business action: Jira ticket creation
POST http://127.0.0.1:8000/ask
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "question": "Create a Jira ticket for urgent customer escalation because checkout payments are failing",
  "user_email": "daniel.chen@example-enterprise.com",
  "conversation_id": "demo-conversation"
}

### Challenging query: ambiguous action
POST http://127.0.0.1:8000/ask
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "question": "Create a ticket",
  "user_email": "daniel.chen@example-enterprise.com",
  "conversation_id": "demo-conversation"
}

### Guarded action: update ticket
POST http://127.0.0.1:8000/ask
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "question": "Update ticket HELP-123 to say customer impact is confirmed",
  "user_email": "priya.sharma@example-enterprise.com",
  "conversation_id": "demo-conversation"
}

### Guarded action: delete denied
POST http://127.0.0.1:8000/ask
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "question": "Delete ticket HELP-123",
  "user_email": "priya.sharma@example-enterprise.com",
  "conversation_id": "demo-conversation"
}

### Confluence-style meeting doc read
POST http://127.0.0.1:8000/ask
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "question": "Read meeting docs for 2026-07-03",
  "conversation_id": "demo-conversation"
}

### RAG over enterprise meeting logs
POST http://127.0.0.1:8000/ask
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "question": "What action item came out of the Acme dashboard latency meeting?",
  "conversation_id": "demo-conversation"
}

### Create Jira ticket from explicit meeting docs
POST http://127.0.0.1:8000/ask
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "question": "Create a Jira ticket from meeting docs on 2026-07-01",
  "user_email": "daniel.chen@example-enterprise.com",
  "conversation_id": "demo-conversation"
}

### Follow-up action using memory: "this" means the last retrieved Confluence context
POST http://127.0.0.1:8000/ask
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "question": "Create a Jira ticket from this",
  "user_email": "daniel.chen@example-enterprise.com",
  "conversation_id": "demo-conversation"
}
